President Biden expressed his deep-rooted love for Israel during a ceremony at the President's Residence Garden in Jerusalem. He highlighted the strong relationship between the United States and Israel, mentioning that over the past 50 years, the bond between the two countries has grown stronger. Biden praised Israel's achievements, including making the desert bloom and developing the Iron Dome. He emphasized that Israel is a nation that will never dwell alone, as long as the United States is there to support it. Biden also reaffirmed America's commitment to Israel's security, stating that it is a responsibility shared by leaders to nurture the bond between the two countries. President Herzog then presented Biden with the Presidential Medal of Honor, recognizing his consistent support for Israel and his dedication to its security. Biden expressed his gratitude and ended his speech with a quote from Irish poet Seamus Heaney, expressing his belief that hope and history can rhyme once more.